<h1 class="header animated fadeIn"><a>Privacy Policy</a></h1>

<div class="container-flex legal-content">
  <div class="legal-section animated fadeIn" style="animation-delay: 0.1s;">
    <h2 class="textiboi">Introduction</h2>
    <p class="textiboi">
      Last Updated: February 12, 2026
    </p>
    <p class="textiboi">
      This Privacy Policy describes how the Package Tracking application
      ("the App") handles
      your information. LeonimusT is committed to protecting your privacy and
      ensuring transparency
      about our data practices.
    </p>
    <p class="textiboi">
      Please read this Privacy Policy carefully to understand how we handle your
      data when you use
      our App.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="legal-section animated fadeIn" style="animation-delay: 0.2s;">
    <h2 class="textiboi">Data We Collect</h2>
    <p class="textiboi">
      The Package Tracking app collects and processes the following information
      to provide tracking services:
    </p>
    <ul class="textiboi">
      <li><strong>Package Tracking Numbers:</strong> The tracking numbers you
        enter to monitor your shipments</li>
      <li><strong>Carrier Information:</strong> The shipping carrier(s)
        associated with your packages (e.g., UPS, FedEx, USPS, DHL)</li>
      <li><strong>Authentication Tokens:</strong> API credentials or
        authorization tokens required to access carrier tracking services</li>
      <li><strong>Tracking History:</strong> Status updates, delivery events,
        and location information retrieved from carriers</li>
      <li><strong>Device Tokens:</strong> Identifiers needed to send push
        notifications about package status changes</li>
      <li><strong>Timestamps:</strong> When you add packages, when status
        checks occur, and when updates are received</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="textiboi">
      All data is stored <strong>locally on your device</strong>. We do not
      store your tracking data on our servers.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="legal-section animated fadeIn" style="animation-delay: 0.3s;">
    <h2 class="textiboi">How We Use Your Data</h2>
    <p class="textiboi">
      The information collected is used exclusively for the following purposes:
    </p>
    <ul class="textiboi">
      <li>To retrieve tracking information from shipping carrier APIs</li>
      <li>To display current delivery status and shipment updates</li>
      <li>To send push notifications when package status changes</li>
      <li>To maintain a local history of your tracked packages</li>
      <li>To authenticate with carrier tracking services on your behalf</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="textiboi">
      We do not use your data for marketing, advertising, analytics, or any
      purpose beyond providing the core tracking functionality.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="legal-section animated fadeIn" style="animation-delay: 0.4s;">
    <h2 class="textiboi">Third-Party Services and Data Sharing</h2>
    <p class="textiboi">
      To function, the App must transmit data to third-party shipping carrier
      APIs. When you track a package:
    </p>
    <ul class="textiboi">
      <li>Your tracking number is sent to the respective carrier's API</li>
      <li>Authentication tokens (if provided) are transmitted to verify
        access</li>
      <li>The carrier processes your request and returns tracking
        information</li>
      <li>This data is then stored locally on your device</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="textiboi">
      <strong>Carriers we integrate with may include:</strong> UPS, FedEx, USPS,
      DHL, and other shipping services. Each carrier has its own privacy policy
      and terms of service governing how they handle tracking requests.
    </p>
    <p class="textiboi">
      <strong>Important:</strong> We do not control these third-party services.
      When you use carrier tracking APIs through our App, you are subject to
      their privacy policies and data practices. We recommend reviewing the
      privacy policies of any carriers you use:
    </p>
    <ul class="textiboi">
      <li>Tracking numbers may be logged by carrier systems</li>
      <li>Carriers may associate requests with IP addresses or device
        information</li>
      <li>Carrier privacy policies govern their data retention and usage</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="legal-section animated fadeIn" style="animation-delay: 0.5s;">
    <h2 class="textiboi">Local Data Storage</h2>
    <p class="textiboi">
      Despite transmitting data to carrier APIs for tracking purposes,
      <strong>all your package information is stored locally on your
        device</strong>:
    </p>
    <ul class="textiboi">
      <li>Your tracking numbers and history remain on your device</li>
      <li>Authentication tokens are stored locally in secure device storage</li>
      <li>We do not have access to your package data</li>
      <li>Your tracking information is not uploaded to our servers or cloud
        services</li>
      <li>No user accounts are created or maintained on our systems</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="legal-section animated fadeIn" style="animation-delay: 0.6s;">
    <h2 class="textiboi">Push Notifications</h2>
    <p class="textiboi">
      If you enable push notifications, the App collects and uses:
    </p>
    <ul class="textiboi">
      <li><strong>Device Tokens:</strong> Unique identifiers provided by Apple
        Push Notification Service (APNs) or Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM)</li>
      <li><strong>Notification Preferences:</strong> Your settings for which
        updates trigger notifications</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="textiboi">
      Notifications are sent when package status changes are detected. You can
      disable notifications at any time in the App settings or your device
      system settings.
    </p>
    <p class="textiboi">
      Push notification services (APNs/FCM) may process device tokens according
      to their own privacy policies. LeonimusT does not control how Apple or
      Google handle notification delivery.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="legal-section animated fadeIn" style="animation-delay: 0.7s;">
    <h2 class="textiboi">Service Availability and Data Accuracy</h2>
    <p class="textiboi">
      The App relies on third-party carrier APIs for tracking information.
      Please be aware:
    </p>
    <ul class="textiboi">
      <li>Tracking accuracy depends on data provided by carriers</li>
      <li>Information may be delayed, incomplete, or temporarily
        unavailable</li>
      <li>Carrier APIs may experience downtime or service interruptions</li>
      <li>We do not guarantee real-time or error-free tracking data</li>
      <li>Rate limiting may affect how frequently tracking information is
        updated</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="textiboi">
      LeonimusT is not responsible for the accuracy, completeness, or
      availability of tracking information provided by third-party carriers.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="legal-section animated fadeIn" style="animation-delay: 0.8s;">
    <h2 class="textiboi">No Analytics or Advertising</h2>
    <p class="textiboi">
      The App does not integrate with any analytics services, advertising
      networks, or data collection platforms. This includes:
    </p>
    <ul class="textiboi">
      <li>No analytics services (Google Analytics, Mixpanel, etc.)</li>
      <li>No advertising networks or ad tracking</li>
      <li>No social media integrations</li>
      <li>No crash reporting services that transmit personal data</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="textiboi">
      The only external connections are to carrier tracking APIs (as described
      above) and push notification services (if enabled).
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="legal-section animated fadeIn" style="animation-delay: 0.9s;">
    <h2 class="textiboi">No User Accounts</h2>
    <p class="textiboi">
      The Package Tracking app does not require or support user accounts,
      authentication,
      or login systems. You can use the App anonymously without providing any
      personal
      identification information such as name, email, or phone number.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="legal-section animated fadeIn" style="animation-delay: 1s;">
    <h2 class="textiboi">Data Security</h2>
    <p class="textiboi">
      We take reasonable measures to protect your data:
    </p>
    <ul class="textiboi">
      <li><strong>Encryption in Transit:</strong> All API communications use
        HTTPS/TLS encryption to protect data during transmission</li>
      <li><strong>Local Storage Security:</strong> Tracking data and
        authentication tokens are stored using secure device storage
        mechanisms</li>
      <li><strong>No Cloud Storage:</strong> Your tracking information is never
        uploaded to remote servers</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="textiboi">
      Since data is stored locally on your device, the security of your
      information also depends on:
    </p>
    <ul class="textiboi">
      <li>Device lock screens and passwords</li>
      <li>Operating system security settings</li>
      <li>Device encryption (if available)</li>
      <li>Physical security of your device</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="textiboi">
      We recommend ensuring your device has appropriate security measures
      enabled to protect your
      locally stored tracking data and authentication tokens.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="legal-section animated fadeIn" style="animation-delay: 1.1s;">
    <h2 class="textiboi">Data Retention</h2>
    <p class="textiboi">
      Your tracking data is stored locally on your device for as long as you
      choose:
    </p>
    <ul class="textiboi">
      <li>You can manually delete individual packages or tracking history at any
        time</li>
      <li>All data is removed when you uninstall the App</li>
      <li>No tracking data is retained on our servers (we don't have servers for
        your data)</li>
      <li>Carrier APIs may retain logs of tracking requests according to their
        own policies</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="legal-section animated fadeIn" style="animation-delay: 1.2s;">
    <h2 class="textiboi">Data Backup and Loss</h2>
    <p class="textiboi">
      Because the App stores data locally without cloud backup, you are
      responsible for backing up
      your data. LeonimusT cannot recover lost data if:
    </p>
    <ul class="textiboi">
      <li>Your device is lost, stolen, or damaged</li>
      <li>You uninstall the App without backing up your data</li>
      <li>Your device experiences a system failure or data corruption</li>
      <li>You reset or replace your device</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="textiboi">
      We recommend regularly exporting your tracking data (if the App provides
      this feature)
      or using your device's built-in backup solutions.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="legal-section animated fadeIn" style="animation-delay: 1.3s;">
    <h2 class="textiboi">Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p class="textiboi">
      The App collects tracking numbers and related information as described in
      this policy. While no personally identifiable information is required to
      use the App, we recommend parental guidance for users under 13.
    </p>
    <p class="textiboi">
      Parents should supervise children's use of the App and ensure they
      understand what information is being shared with carrier APIs.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="legal-section animated fadeIn" style="animation-delay: 1.4s;">
    <h2 class="textiboi">Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p class="textiboi">
      We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in
      our practices or
      for legal, operational, or regulatory reasons. Any changes will be posted
      on this page with
      an updated "Last Updated" date.
    </p>
    <p class="textiboi">
      If we make significant changes that affect how we handle your information,
      we will notify
      users through appropriate channels (such as an in-app notice or website
      announcement).
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="legal-section animated fadeIn" style="animation-delay: 1.5s;">
    <h2 class="textiboi">Your Rights</h2>
    <p class="textiboi">
      Since the Package Tracking app stores data locally on your device:
    </p>
    <ul class="textiboi">
      <li>You have complete control over your tracking data at all times</li>
      <li>You can delete individual packages or all tracking history within the
        App</li>
      <li>You can uninstall the App to remove all locally stored data</li>
      <li>There is no data to request, export, or delete from our systems
        (because we don't store your data)</li>
      <li>You can revoke push notification permissions at any time</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="textiboi">
      For data held by carrier APIs, you must contact the respective carriers
      directly to exercise your data rights.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="legal-section animated fadeIn" style="animation-delay: 1.6s;">
    <h2 class="textiboi">Solana dApp Store Distribution</h2>
    <p class="textiboi">
      The Package Tracking app is distributed through the Solana dApp Store.
      Please note
      that the dApp Store itself may have its own privacy policies and data
      collection practices
      separate from this App. We recommend reviewing the Solana dApp Store's
      privacy policy for
      information about their data practices.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="legal-section animated fadeIn" style="animation-delay: 1.7s;">
    <h2 class="textiboi">Contact Information</h2>
    <p class="textiboi">
      If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy
